1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:43,060
(Weaving Flower Baskets)

3
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:47,490
Does this go with this?

4
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:49,459
No, this one goes with this.

5
00:01:49,460 --> 00:01:49,819
No.

6
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:51,490
That's the previous step.

7
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:54,210
This one goes with this.

8
00:02:03,020 --> 00:02:05,379
Why don't you go to sleep, Xiu'er?
I'm here.

9
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:07,530
No, I haven't finished weaving yet.

10
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:08,619
Go to sleep.

11
00:02:08,620 --> 00:02:09,259
When you wake up,

12
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:10,499
I'll have finished weaving

13
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:11,690
this flower basket for you.

14
00:02:13,620 --> 00:02:14,810
Here.

15
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:22,459
Tuck yourself in.

16
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:23,650
Alright.

17
00:02:26,580 --> 00:02:27,770
Put your hands inside.

18
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,490
Tuck yourself in.

19
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,330
Close your eyes.

20
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:47,499
It's too tiring to weave it yourself.

21
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,170
I want to accompany you.

22
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:51,280
You can accompany me
even with your eyes closed.

23
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,259
I paid so much tuition

24
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:55,539
to your embroidery house,

25
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:57,050
but I'm the one getting trained.

26
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:00,499
Close your eyes.

27
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:01,690
I'm looking at you.

28
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:27,899
What about yours?

29
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,170
Mine is prettier.

30
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:33,899
How pretty.

31
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,779
It's evenly woven

32
00:03:34,780 --> 00:03:36,219
and neatly shaped.

33
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:37,579
How beautiful.

34
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:39,099
How did you weave your flower basket?

35
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:39,899
Teach us.

36
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:40,499
Yes.

37
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:41,739
- Teach us.
- Teach us.

38
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:42,699
Xiu'er.

39
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,259
Did you really weave

40
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:46,010
such a beautiful flower basket yourself?

41
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:48,419
When my mother bought tofu

42
00:03:48,420 --> 00:03:49,939
early in the morning,

43
00:03:49,940 --> 00:03:50,979
she saw your father

44
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,499
buying a flower basket nearby.

45
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:53,459
Impossible.

46
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,259
I...

47
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,859
Did you really weave this yourself?

48
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,170
Give it back!

49
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,779
You must have bought it.

50
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,019
My mother came back and said

51
00:04:00,020 --> 00:04:01,899
your father's bargaining skills

52
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,530
attracted a lot of attention.

53
00:04:03,820 --> 00:04:05,219
Don't say that about my father.

54
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:05,979
Did you make

55
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:07,330
the flower baskets yourselves?

56
00:04:07,380 --> 00:04:08,019
Give it back!

57
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:09,859
My mother made flower basket for me.

58
00:04:09,860 --> 00:04:10,459
Yes, mine too.

59
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:11,459
Mine too.

60
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:13,560
Won't your mother help you
weave the flower basket?

61
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,219
I heard her mother died of illness.

62
00:04:15,220 --> 00:04:17,139
Her father must have bought
this flower basket

63
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:18,730
from the market!

64
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:21,459
Xiu'er's father is good at bargaining.

65
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:23,339
He bought a flower basket to fool her.

66
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:24,890
Don't say that about my father!

67
00:04:25,860 --> 00:04:27,170
Don't grab it.

68
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:28,419
Xiu'er.

69
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,650
Give it back!

70
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,019
No.

71
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:44,059
How dare you smile?

72
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:45,219
Why are you looking at me?

73
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,570
Who should I look at then?

74
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:50,810
What does it taste like?

75
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:52,419
It's salty.

76
00:04:52,420 --> 00:04:53,690
Salty.

77
00:04:54,300 --> 00:04:55,890
No, how many people beat you up?

78
00:04:56,020 --> 00:04:57,210
Six.

79
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,690
Six?

80
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,979
Six people beat you,
and you're still smiling.

81
00:05:01,980 --> 00:05:03,099
Who won?

82
00:05:03,100 --> 00:05:04,290
I won.

83
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:06,210
Six people beat you, and you won?

84
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:07,779
How are

85
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:08,819
the others?

86
00:05:08,820 --> 00:05:09,739
You didn't see it.

87
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:11,650
Some of them have swollen eyes.

88
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:13,970
Swollen eyes?

89
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:16,099
No, why did you

90
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,290
fight?

91
00:05:17,540 --> 00:05:18,619
Because of the flower basket.

92
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:20,379
They were jealous
of my beautiful flower basket

93
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:22,499
and stepped on the flower basket
that you wove.

94
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,259
They also said
you didn't weave it yourself.

95
00:05:24,260 --> 00:05:25,810
I was so angry.

96
00:05:28,260 --> 00:05:30,170
It's just a flower basket.

97
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:31,619
No.

98
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:32,179
I'll

99
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:33,459
weave another one for you.

100
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:34,059
Really?

101
00:05:34,060 --> 00:05:35,179
You'll weave it yourself?

102
00:05:35,180 --> 00:05:36,370
I'll weave it myself.

103
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,299
Keep in mind
that you can't fight anymore.

104
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:38,939
Got it?

105
00:05:38,940 --> 00:05:40,219
Sure, it's a deal.

106
00:05:40,220 --> 00:05:40,899
It's a deal?

107
00:05:40,900 --> 00:05:42,730
Who did you inherit this temper from?

108
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,800
Who did you inherit this temper from?

109
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,930
From Mother.

110
00:05:48,340 --> 00:05:48,899
It's a deal.

111
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,330
Here, seal the deal with blood.

112
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:56,560
=Episode 7=

113
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:58,530
(Lower A Hall)

114
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,019
Miss.

115
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:11,410
Mr. Zheng asked to see you.

116
00:06:12,220 --> 00:06:13,450
You came just in time.

117
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,210
I have something life-threatening
to tell you.

118
00:06:15,260 --> 00:06:16,450
I know.

119
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:19,090
Li Shande's life is in danger.

120
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,819
With his stubborn character

121
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:22,659
that won't listen to anything,

122
00:06:22,660 --> 00:06:24,200
something bad will happen
sooner or later.

123
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,499
It's all his own fault.

124
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,459
Let him fend for himself.

125
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:27,650
It's not him.

126
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:28,539
He's lucky.

127
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:29,770
He's safe for now.

128
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:31,600
I'll pass a message to Zhao Xinmin

129
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,920
and tell him that Li Shande
isn't aligned with Left Chancellor

130
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,010
and remove his concerns.

131
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,450
You said it's life-threatening.

132
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,370
Whose life is it?

133
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:42,939
Your life

134
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:44,130
is under threat.

135
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,290
Miss, you're such a joker.

136
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:51,490
How could it be...

137
00:06:52,780 --> 00:06:54,330
How could it be so sudden?

138
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,890
Right Chancellor
sent a new envoy to Lingnan.

139
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:57,899
As soon as he sees you,

140
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,650
he'll see right through your identity.

141
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:02,050
He'll see right my identity?

142
00:07:05,460 --> 00:07:06,970
Fortunately, the journey is long.

143
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:10,210
We still have time to maneuver.

144
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:12,339
The new envoy has left Chang'an

145
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,419
for over 20 days.

146
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:14,770
Counting the time,

147
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:16,259
he should be in Lingnan soon.

148
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:17,539
Stop him!

149
00:07:17,540 --> 00:07:18,939
I already sent experts

150
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,850
to intercept him near Xiang River.

151
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:24,090
Unfortunately, the envoy was skilled
in martial arts and escaped several times.

152
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:26,099
Later, he changed his route

153
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,370
and hid his whereabouts.

154
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:28,859
I arranged people

155
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:29,699
to ambush

156
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,170
at the main path into Lingnan.

157
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:33,139
This is our last chance.

158
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:35,170
It's also your last chance of survival.

159
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:37,970
We must seize this chance.

160
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,339
Make sure it's foolproof.

161
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:41,179
Don't be stingy
with your forces and money.

162
00:07:41,180 --> 00:07:42,799
Attack from all directions.

163
00:07:42,799 --> 00:07:44,539
I don't believe he can
fight 100 people alone.

164
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,379
Zheng Ping'an.

165
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:47,259
Favored by Left Chancellor

166
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:48,939
and entrusted by Security Bureau
to help you,

167
00:07:48,940 --> 00:07:50,290
Konglang Guild will do our best.

168
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:51,779
If you want to live,

169
00:07:51,780 --> 00:07:54,739
you must get the letter
of allegiance tomorrow and leave Lingnan.

170
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:55,499
Otherwise,

171
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,890
once this new envoy steps
into Inspector's Office,

172
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:00,970
you'll lose your life.

173
00:08:13,300 --> 00:08:14,490
Let me see.

174
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:16,970
What happened?

175
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:18,170
Mr. Li.

176
00:08:19,420 --> 00:08:20,610
Tell me.

177
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:21,979
You're still energetic

178
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:22,979
just half a day ago,

179
00:08:22,980 --> 00:08:25,170
now you're suddenly sick?

180
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:29,490
Qilang went out for a while

181
00:08:29,620 --> 00:08:31,450
and came back burning up.

182
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:34,130
Maybe he caught a cold.

183
00:08:34,140 --> 00:08:34,979
Nonsense.

184
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,219
How can you catch a cold here?

185
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:37,530
He has heat stroke.

186
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:43,019
I know

187
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:45,170
you're so worried about my life

188
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,490
that you're stressed out.

189
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,610
Sit farther away from me

190
00:08:54,780 --> 00:08:56,210
so that I can feel better.

191
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,530
Is it hot?

192
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:59,179
It's hot. Hurry.

193
00:08:59,180 --> 00:08:59,899
Let's ventilate it.

194
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,099
You can't cover yourself.

195
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:03,819
It's cold now. Covering yourself
will only make you feel warmer.

196
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,010
Gou'er.

197
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:06,459
Pull up the curtains

198
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,659
on these windows.

199
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:08,850
Ventilate it.

200
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:10,090
It's hot.

201
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:12,970
Here, move.

202
00:09:12,980 --> 00:09:14,170
Move.

203
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:16,530
I know everything.

204
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,050
Although I'm afraid of death,

205
00:09:21,260 --> 00:09:22,970
I'm not a coward.

206
00:09:23,260 --> 00:09:24,379
We can't collapse

207
00:09:24,380 --> 00:09:25,730
just because

208
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:28,299
we're about to die.

209
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,490
Right?

210
00:09:35,140 --> 00:09:36,330
Are you feeling better?

211
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,450
I had my fortune told when I was a kid.

212
00:09:45,540 --> 00:09:47,179
The fortune teller said

213
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:48,619
my fate

214
00:09:48,620 --> 00:09:51,170
is to survive desperate times.

215
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,450
I won't die.

216
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:55,250
And I have a skill.

217
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:59,170
I can transfer this bad luck
to someone else.

218
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,490
What are you happy about?

219
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:07,730
Say something helpful,

220
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,730
or get lost.

221
00:10:09,940 --> 00:10:11,410
Aren't I comforting you?

222
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:12,730
Is this comforting?

223
00:10:13,540 --> 00:10:15,419
You transfer bad luck to others.

224
00:10:15,420 --> 00:10:16,850
Others want to live.

225
00:10:17,940 --> 00:10:19,450
Why are you so agitated?

226
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:21,659
I only said I can transfer bad luck

227
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:22,659
to someone else.

228
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:23,899
You can't blame me, can you?

229
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:26,779
You can only say
that this person has little luck, right?

230
00:10:26,780 --> 00:10:29,370
He's unlucky short-lived.

231
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:33,410
Who are you calling unlucky

232
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,530
and short-lived?

233
00:10:37,780 --> 00:10:38,970
Get out.

234
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,490
You...

235
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:45,579
You're not stressed out.

236
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,450
You're possessed.

237
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,930
You won't even listen to my advice.

238
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,179
Mr. Li.

239
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:52,850
Stop persuading him.

240
00:10:54,740 --> 00:10:56,170
Fine, I'll get him some medicine.

241
00:10:56,260 --> 00:10:57,450
Take good care of him.

242
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:14,370
Qilang.

243
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:16,610
Mr. Li is thickheaded,

244
00:11:17,020 --> 00:11:19,290
but he's sincere to you.

245
00:11:19,660 --> 00:11:20,259
Look.

246
00:11:20,260 --> 00:11:21,179
Once he starts fiddling

247
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:22,579
with litchis,

248
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:24,450
he forgets about everything else.

249
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:26,179
But he ran out

250
00:11:26,180 --> 00:11:27,410
to buy medicine for you.

251
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:30,730
Mr. Li is a good man.

252
00:11:32,820 --> 00:11:34,010
Gou'er.

253
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:36,490
- Coming.
- Come here.

254
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:39,890
Qilang.

255
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,570
Get out too.

256
00:11:56,260 --> 00:12:03,259
(Siling Apothecary)

257
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:04,579
He opens late.

258
00:12:04,580 --> 00:12:05,970
Maybe he'll be here soon.

259
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,330
Your flower basket is well-woven.

260
00:12:21,100 --> 00:12:22,930
You're from Chang'an.

261
00:12:23,060 --> 00:12:24,690
Would you like to buy a flower basket?

262
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:26,259
Judging from your reply,

263
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,650
are you also from Chang'an?

264
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:29,619
It's hard to change my accent.

265
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:32,050
I'm indeed from Chang'an.

266
00:12:32,780 --> 00:12:34,530
Why are you here?

267
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:37,099
My husband

268
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:39,210
was originally an official
in Ministry of Revenue.

269
00:12:39,260 --> 00:12:40,939
He offended Right Chancellor,

270
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:43,050
and the whole family was exiled here.

271
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:44,219
He died a few years ago.

272
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:46,010
I don't know how to do anything else.

273
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,059
I can only do this

274
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:51,730
to make ends meet.

275
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:09,050
How did you get around that just now?

276
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:13,930
A grown man like you
wants to learn this?

277
00:13:20,180 --> 00:13:21,850
I'll come back another day
to ask for advice.

278
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,370
You got it wrong.

279
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:43,890
You have good eyesight.

280
00:13:44,740 --> 00:13:45,579
Your brain

281
00:13:45,580 --> 00:13:47,379
works faster than my abacus.

282
00:13:47,380 --> 00:13:49,299
This minor calculation is not a big deal.

283
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:52,019
Sir. We ran out of Solomon's Seal.

284
00:13:52,020 --> 00:13:53,299
We can't fill

285
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,490
this prescription.

286
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:58,370
I forgot.

287
00:13:58,660 --> 00:13:59,859
Sir.

288
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,539
Solomon's Seal was sold to Hu merchants

289
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,059
a few days ago.

290
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:04,139
All of it?

291
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,490
I sold all of it.

292
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:07,579
They're in the spice business.

293
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:08,819
Spices are afraid of moisture.

294
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:11,760
Putting a few pieces of Solomon's Seal
beside the spices can prevent moisture.

295
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,170
They have a lot of spices in stock,

296
00:14:13,340 --> 00:14:15,050
so they bought all the Solomon's Seal.

297
00:14:15,540 --> 00:14:16,219
You...

298
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:18,650
How about I change it to Glehnia Root?

299
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:21,210
What about the price?

300
00:14:21,380 --> 00:14:22,970
It's the same price.

301
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:24,490
Alright.

302
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:29,530
(Siling Apothecary)

303
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,810
(Glehnia Root)

304
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,410
Why is this urn double-layered?

305
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,459
Yes, it is.

306
00:14:46,460 --> 00:14:48,130
Where did you buy this urn?

307
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,130
I've never seen it in Lingnan either.

308
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:52,170
I heard only Hu merchants have it.

309
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:52,739
When I

310
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:54,690
went to deliver
Solomon's Seal yesterday,

311
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:56,810
I saw them using this to store spices.

312
00:14:57,260 --> 00:15:00,250
It's very effective in preventing spices
from deteriorating and volatilizing.

313
00:15:01,260 --> 00:15:05,290
I thought it would be suitable
to store moisture-sensitive medicine.

314
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:06,739
Do they still have

315
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:07,979
more urns?

316
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,330
They have lots,

317
00:15:09,340 --> 00:15:11,339
but I heard they're disposing them.

318
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,530
Where?

319
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:21,979
Where's Su?

320
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:23,170
He's in there.

321
00:15:27,580 --> 00:15:29,690
Su, we got news.

322
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,290
Someone shipped the goods.

323
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:33,299
Really?

324
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:34,059
Yes.

325
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:35,530
Are you sure it's our goods?

326
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:37,770
It's our Benzoin.

327
00:15:39,380 --> 00:15:40,890
Who shipped it?

328
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:43,010
It's Amita.

329
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:03,059
At the beginning of next month,

330
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:04,179
Hu Merchants' Association

331
00:16:04,180 --> 00:16:05,930
will elect a new leader.

332
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,850
All the Hu merchants will gather.

333
00:16:09,220 --> 00:16:11,210
Whoever can bring the best business

334
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:11,899
can be elected

335
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,890
as the new leader.

336
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,490
I hope you won't miss this opportunity.

337
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:19,690
No matter who gets all the attention,

338
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:20,779
no one can shake

339
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,139
Amita's status.

340
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:25,640
(Amita, Leader of Hu Merchants' Association)
During Amita's tenure as leader,

341
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:28,490
our association has doubled in size.

342
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:31,530
The variety of goods also increased.

343
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:33,619
Everyone knows

344
00:16:33,620 --> 00:16:34,779
about these accomplishments.

345
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:36,210
We should elect Amita

346
00:16:36,380 --> 00:16:38,170
as leader.

347
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:41,459
When Su was leader

348
00:16:41,460 --> 00:16:43,219
in the earlier years,

349
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:45,970
we're friends with Tang people.

350
00:16:46,020 --> 00:16:49,050
We never need
to watch their moods to do business.

351
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,450
But in recent years,

352
00:16:50,540 --> 00:16:52,770
the association's direction
has changed.

353
00:16:53,020 --> 00:16:54,099
But we Hu merchants

354
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:56,210
do business on Tang territory,

355
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:58,219
how can we avoid Tang people

356
00:16:58,220 --> 00:17:00,090
and mind our own business?

357
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,579
The association exists

358
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:03,490
to safeguard
the Hu merchants' interests.

359
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:04,619
This direction

360
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:06,170
will never change.

361
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:08,810
The leader

362
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,050
speaks as beautifully as a singing bird.

363
00:17:15,740 --> 00:17:16,930
Su.

364
00:17:17,580 --> 00:17:19,290
What wind brought you here?

365
00:17:21,580 --> 00:17:22,810
An evil wind.

366
00:17:24,020 --> 00:17:25,210
A demonic wind.

367
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:27,050
The wind of stealing.

368
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:28,730
The wind of robbery.

369
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:31,699
Sounds like

370
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:33,330
your stance has changed.

371
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:34,619
I remember

372
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:37,210
you loved to say
that harmony brings wealth.

373
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,930
How come you're so hostile

374
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:41,370
after not meeting for a few years?

375
00:17:41,580 --> 00:17:42,970
We haven't met for a few years.

376
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:46,090
You're also completely different.

377
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,730
You changed with each new day.

378
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:54,090
All our old friends are here.

379
00:17:55,060 --> 00:17:57,290
Tell me

380
00:17:58,660 --> 00:18:00,610
why you stole my Benzoin.

381
00:18:02,860 --> 00:18:04,490
You can misuse idioms,

382
00:18:04,940 --> 00:18:06,410
but watch your mouth.

383
00:18:07,180 --> 00:18:09,850
You said I stole your spices.

384
00:18:11,420 --> 00:18:12,610
Do you have any evidence?

385
00:18:19,460 --> 00:18:20,650
Leader!

386
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:23,850
Leader.

387
00:18:23,900 --> 00:18:27,290
Su sent someone to forcibly intercept our spices
and insisted that they're his.

388
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:35,619
Tell me why my spices
has just disappeared,

389
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:36,810
and your spices

390
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:38,690
appeared on the market.

391
00:18:38,740 --> 00:18:40,130
Is this what they call

392
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:42,250
there's no story without a coincidence?

393
00:18:43,500 --> 00:18:44,690
Su.

394
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:46,770
You've been gone for too long.

395
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:48,499
You no longer

396
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,659
monopolize the spice business.

397
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:53,370
My spices are stored
in double-layer urns.

398
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:55,530
In Lingnan,

399
00:18:55,820 --> 00:18:57,050
only my family

400
00:18:57,420 --> 00:18:59,210
has double-layer urns.

401
00:19:00,060 --> 00:19:01,250
Amita.

402
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:04,290
Do you dare to open the box?

403
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:06,650
Whether it's Su Liang's goods

404
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:07,819
will be clear

405
00:19:07,820 --> 00:19:08,659
and obvious.

406
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:10,170
The truth can be revealed.

407
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:11,930
Leader.

408
00:19:16,980 --> 00:19:18,330
Get our goods.

409
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:28,530
(Village Warehouse)

410
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:48,250
Double-layer urns.

411
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:50,610
Double-layer urns.

412
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:56,850
I'll put litchis in this

413
00:19:57,340 --> 00:19:58,890
and pour water outside.

414
00:19:59,580 --> 00:20:01,570
A unified double-layer.
Stable under motion.

415
00:20:02,540 --> 00:20:03,850
These are good urns.

416
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:06,370
Good urns.

417
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:11,290
Who is it?

418
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:13,490
What are you doing here?

419
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:14,770
I want to buy urns.

420
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:16,379
I'm not selling these urns.

421
00:20:16,380 --> 00:20:17,570
Leave.

422
00:20:17,820 --> 00:20:19,490
Let me introduce myself.

423
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:22,570
I'm the Litchi Envoy
appointed by His Majesty.

424
00:20:22,940 --> 00:20:25,139
I'm in charge of transporting litchis.

425
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,850
What Litchi Envoy?

426
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:29,210
What does it have to do with me?

427
00:20:29,940 --> 00:20:32,659
Litchi Envoy.
It doesn't matter what envoy you are.

428
00:20:32,660 --> 00:20:33,899
I'm telling you.

429
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,299
I'm not selling these urns.

430
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:36,419
Next time

431
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,850
you want to go out

432
00:20:37,980 --> 00:20:39,139
and flaunt your authority,

433
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:41,699
ask around and find out
their background first.

434
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,379
Be careful, or you'll lose your job

435
00:20:43,380 --> 00:20:45,130
and regret it forever.

436
00:20:45,420 --> 00:20:47,210
I'll be burning incense in gratitude

437
00:20:47,340 --> 00:20:48,690
if I can step down from this job.

438
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,690
Are you provoking me?

439
00:20:50,860 --> 00:20:52,130
No.

440
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:55,379
- Do you think I can't make you lose your job?
- Who's disturbing my rest?

441
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:56,570
Wait here.

442
00:20:57,380 --> 00:20:58,139
Captain Yang.

443
00:20:58,140 --> 00:20:59,330
This guy.

444
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:01,299
I'm

445
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:03,059
the Litchi Envoy
appointed by His Majesty!

446
00:21:03,060 --> 00:21:04,570
(Litchi Bureau)
Shut up!

447
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:05,779
Look.

448
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:07,139
A ninth-rank official

449
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,259
flaunting his authority
like he's a prime minister.

450
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:10,450
This...

451
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:15,579
Envoy Li.

452
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:16,770
Captain Yang.

453
00:21:17,260 --> 00:21:19,330
It's fate.

454
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:23,899
Su.

455
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,210
You'd better watch carefully.

456
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:28,370
This isn't your double-layer urn.

457
00:21:43,780 --> 00:21:45,739
It's not my double-layer urn,

458
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:47,650
but it's my Benzoin.

459
00:21:48,820 --> 00:21:52,179
After sailing thousands of miles by sea,
the fragrance does not fade

460
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:53,419
and maintain

461
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:54,810
80% quality.

462
00:21:54,940 --> 00:21:55,859
Except for me,

463
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:57,210
who in Lingnan

464
00:21:57,540 --> 00:21:58,930
can do it?

465
00:21:59,380 --> 00:22:00,570
Amita.

466
00:22:00,700 --> 00:22:01,579
You

467
00:22:01,580 --> 00:22:03,250
replaced my double-layer urn

468
00:22:03,580 --> 00:22:05,450
and stole my Benzoin.

469
00:22:08,980 --> 00:22:10,859
Su, you're my elder.

470
00:22:10,860 --> 00:22:13,050
That's why I let you open the box
and inspect the goods.

471
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:16,610
It would be disappointing

472
00:22:17,860 --> 00:22:20,050
if you shamelessly frame me.

473
00:22:20,660 --> 00:22:22,050
If that's the case,

474
00:22:22,060 --> 00:22:22,939
don't blame me

475
00:22:22,940 --> 00:22:24,530
for not giving you face.

476
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:26,170
What can you do to me?

477
00:22:26,940 --> 00:22:28,170
I'm not selling

478
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:29,410
these urns.

479
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:31,210
What can you do?

480
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:32,530
I'll raise the price.

481
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,370
Alright.

482
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:39,650
One urn is ten guan.

483
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:42,819
No.

484
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:44,610
You're taking advantage
of the situation.

485
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:45,970
Are you buying it?

486
00:22:48,060 --> 00:22:48,819
Well...

487
00:22:48,820 --> 00:22:50,050
I'm not selling it anymore.

488
00:22:56,780 --> 00:22:57,970
Don't be mad.

489
00:22:58,220 --> 00:22:59,730
It's just one setback.

490
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:01,059
Think

491
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:03,050
about how you treated me last time?

492
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:04,299
I went

493
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,130
to collect the debt with the deed.

494
00:23:06,180 --> 00:23:08,299
I was about to get the litchi garden,

495
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:09,379
yet you appeared

496
00:23:09,380 --> 00:23:11,139
and made it the imperial litchi garden

497
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:12,930
with a wave of the hand.

498
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,419
You turned my deed

499
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:16,290
into a piece of waste paper.

500
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:18,579
You didn't give me

501
00:23:18,580 --> 00:23:20,290
any face.

502
00:23:23,260 --> 00:23:24,810
Didn't I tell you?

503
00:23:25,020 --> 00:23:26,019
If you've got schemes,

504
00:23:26,020 --> 00:23:28,050
go to Chang'an
and scheme against His Majesty.

505
00:23:28,580 --> 00:23:29,899
All bark

506
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:31,099
and no bite.

507
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:32,579
Collect debts from His Majesty?

508
00:23:32,580 --> 00:23:34,330
I don't have a death wish!

509
00:23:34,460 --> 00:23:36,410
I rather smash the urns

510
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:38,330
than sell you one.

511
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:39,299
You picked up

512
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,499
the cargo ship at the port

513
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:42,290
with a travel pass.

514
00:23:43,980 --> 00:23:45,210
May I ask

515
00:23:46,540 --> 00:23:48,250
where you got your pass from?

516
00:23:48,940 --> 00:23:52,859
Inspector's Office recently
only gave Litchi Envoy a blank pass

517
00:23:52,860 --> 00:23:54,499
for the transportation of litchis.

518
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:56,970
That's why he can pass through
without stopping and getting taxed.

519
00:23:59,100 --> 00:23:59,819
Su.

520
00:23:59,820 --> 00:24:01,059
You privately dealt this

521
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:03,010
with Litchi Envoy.

522
00:24:03,820 --> 00:24:04,659
You used to be

523
00:24:04,660 --> 00:24:06,330
the leader of Hu Merchants' Association.

524
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,770
You should know

525
00:24:08,020 --> 00:24:09,850
Hu merchants who broke the rules

526
00:24:10,340 --> 00:24:12,370
will be expelled from Lingnan.

527
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:16,210
You broke the rules today.

528
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:18,650
Shouldn't you set an example?

529
00:24:20,060 --> 00:24:22,130
If you're not selling, I'm not buying!

530
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,090
I declare....

531
00:24:24,820 --> 00:24:25,859
Imperial edict.

532
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:29,379
(Litchi Envoy's Dispatch Imperial Edict)
I declare all double-layer urns in this warehouse

533
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:31,379
are hereby requisitioned
as imperial urns,

534
00:24:31,380 --> 00:24:33,979
specializing in the transportation
of tribute litchis to the north.

535
00:24:33,980 --> 00:24:35,690
These are imperial litchi urns.

536
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:37,979
You scoffed at His Majesty.

537
00:24:37,980 --> 00:24:38,619
Alright.

538
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:40,099
With me here today,

539
00:24:40,100 --> 00:24:41,659
If you smash another double-layer urn,

540
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:44,240
you're messing with His Majesty. Understand?

541
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,800
(Litchi Envoy's Dispatch Imperial Edict)

542
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,099
I sold half of my property

543
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:48,379
to return to Lingnan.

544
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:50,450
I just want to do my own business.

545
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:52,250
I'm not a threat to you.

546
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:53,339
But you

547
00:24:53,340 --> 00:24:55,259
want to control me

548
00:24:55,260 --> 00:24:56,650
and strangle me.

549
00:24:56,940 --> 00:25:00,130
You leave me with nowhere to go,
becoming your prey.

550
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,539
You're young

551
00:25:01,540 --> 00:25:02,619
and beautiful,

552
00:25:02,620 --> 00:25:04,339
but you're too heartless

553
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:05,770
and twisted.

554
00:25:05,860 --> 00:25:07,179
Letting you lead

555
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:08,850
is a tragedy and a disgrace

556
00:25:09,020 --> 00:25:10,210
for the Hu merchants!

557
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:12,290
The Hu merchants' future

558
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:14,330
will never be bright!

559
00:25:14,780 --> 00:25:15,970
Su.

560
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:18,170
This is not the place
for you to act recklessly.

561
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,120
Leader.

562
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:27,099
Litchi Envoy found the double-layer urn
and requisitioned them for imperial use.

563
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,290
Litchi Envoy?

564
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:33,619
- What should we do now?
- Su Liang!

565
00:25:33,620 --> 00:25:34,810
Let's listen to Su.

566
00:25:39,740 --> 00:25:40,459
Do you really want

567
00:25:40,460 --> 00:25:42,290
to do honest business?

568
00:25:42,580 --> 00:25:43,770
Of course.

569
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:46,970
Su Liang's goods were not lost.

570
00:25:56,420 --> 00:25:57,610
What did you say?

571
00:25:58,740 --> 00:26:00,050
Have you forgotten

572
00:26:00,860 --> 00:26:03,010
